narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Private lessons for a serious music student.
I enjoy taking lessons here at Yale.
Voice lessons for credit - amazing way to ensure that you never have to take 5 credits in a semester!
If you can get credit lessons, I would highly recommend them. Even if you don't get a professor, the graduate students are highly qualified to teach. I had a positive experience overall.

I strongly recommend lessons for credit. They are fun, not too much work, rewarding, and tremendously helpful. My voice has undergone a complete transformation since starting. It's helped me develop a much fuller, more mature, operatic sound and given me good habits for vocal health in my other (a cappella, choir) singing commitments. It's low stress and lots of fun.
